  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Clinical recurrence of atrial fibrillation (AF) after catheter ablation</measure>
    <time_frame>after 90 days of catheter ablation and thereafter</time_frame>
    <description>We defined recurrence of AF as any episode of AF or atrial tachycardia lasting longer than 30 sec. Any ECG documentation of AF recurrence after 3 months was diagnosed as clinical recurrence.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
